This article studies the conditions that made possible the association between cinemanovistas and the television journalism area, from the inedited experience of the Globo-Shell Especial documentary series produced the between 1971 and 1973. This program was the precursor of the Globo Reporter. Published in O Globo and in Filme Cultura, the impressions of Geraldo Sarno, Gustavo Dahl, Paulo Gil Soares e Walter Lima Junior regarding their works for the program as much help to raise the question the institutional (re)including of revolutionary artists to the culture industry as to the approximate of two relatively autonomous fields â€“ cinema and television.